I ordered the 730 Burger with bacon and sauteed mushrooms with a side of truffle tots. The truffle tots were very well-seasoned and stayed crunchy in their packaging. The meat of the 730 Burger was fantastic. The freshness of the produce---lettuce, tomato, onion---left a little something to be desired. The sauteed mushrooms were also undercooked. When sauteing mushrooms, it's important to let them seethe all of their moisture in order to eventually develop a crispy brown texture. The raw texture of a garden-variety fungus is not particularly appetizing. The portions were large, and the food was well-packaged. I would say an above-average experience for pub grub.

Now this place saved our day. Ok so I’m not from Boston and I know it’s weird to have soup in the summer but I just wanted to try some Boston white clam chowder. Unfortunately we didn’t get the friendliest of service from other restaurants and it changed my vibe. I gave up on the chowder mission. But my husband insisted I get what I want before our long drive home. He found this restaurant on Google and reviews sounded good. Found parking easy Outside the seating was filled with blooming flowers, this modern tavern was filled with excellent vibes. The staff wasnt held by gun point to work and greeted us asap. The host (Aug 4th, 2019) was incredible sat us down and within 3 minutes a waiter came over and actually knew the menu and had suggestions. Now the truest of test our food, that took less than 10 minutes, to get to our table all I can say is devoured. That clam chowder was perfect and had clams, not just potatoes, perfect seasoning not too salty, creamy or buttery , just right, I felt like Goldilocks! My husband who is vegan ordered the impossible burger and he demolished it. Fries were on point extra crispy and tasty,so yeah, we ate those fries down to the crispy crumbs. I also ordered the side of broccoli with garlic and my 10 month and I wanted to drink the garlic oil lol.  Shout out to my husband, thanks for not giving up cause this Tavern has it, go check it out.
